## The Complete Chat Interface

Replace the contents of your `templates/index.html` with this code:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>My AI Chatbot</title>
    <!-- Bootstrap CSS from CDN -->
    <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.0/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
    <style>
        body {
            background-color: #f8f9fa;
        }
        .chat-container {
            max-width: 600px;
            margin: 50px auto;
        }
        .chat-box {
            height: 400px;
            overflow-y: auto;
            border: 1px solid #dee2e6;
            border-radius: 10px;
            padding: 20px;
            background-color: white;
        }
        .message {
            margin-bottom: 15px;
            padding: 10px 15px;
            border-radius: 15px;
            max-width: 80%;
        }
        .user-message {
            background-color: #007bff;
            color: white;
            margin-left: auto;
        }
        .bot-message {
            background-color: #e9ecef;
            color: #333;
        }
        .message-time {
            font-size: 0.75rem;
            opacity: 0.7;
            margin-top: 5px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="chat-container">
        <div class="card shadow">
            <div class="card-header bg-primary text-white">
                <h4 class="mb-0">🤖 My AI Chatbot</h4>
            </div>
            <div class="card-body">
                <div id="chat-box" class="chat-box">
                    <div class="message bot-message">
                        Hello! I'm your AI assistant. How can I help you today?
                    </div>
                </div>
                <form id="chat-form" class="mt-3">
                    <div class="input-group">
                        <input type="text" 
                               id="message-input" 
                               class="form-control" 
                               placeholder="Type your message..." 
                               autocomplete="off"
                               maxlength="500">
                        <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary">Send</button>
                    </div>
                </form>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Bootstrap JS from CDN -->
    <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.0/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js"></script>

    <!-- Our chat JavaScript -->
    <script>
        const chatForm = document.getElementById('chat-form');
        const messageInput = document.getElementById('message-input');
        const chatBox = document.getElementById('chat-box');

        // Function to add a message to the chat
        function addMessage(text, isUser) {
            const messageDiv = document.createElement('div');
            messageDiv.className = `message ${isUser ? 'user-message' : 'bot-message'}`;
            messageDiv.textContent = text;
            chatBox.appendChild(messageDiv);
            // Scroll to the bottom
            chatBox.scrollTop = chatBox.scrollHeight;
        }

        // Handle form submission
        chatForm.addEventListener('submit', async function(e) {
            e.preventDefault();

            const message = messageInput.value.trim();
            if (!message) return;

            // Add user message to chat
            addMessage(message, true);
            messageInput.value = '';

            try {
                // Send message to Flask backend
                const response = await fetch('/chat', {
                    method: 'POST',
                    headers: {
                        'Content-Type': 'application/json',
                    },
                    body: JSON.stringify({ message: message })
                });

                const data = await response.json();

                // Add bot response to chat
                addMessage(data.response, false);
            } catch (error) {
                addMessage('Sorry, something went wrong. Please try again.', false);
                console.error('Error:', error);
            }
        });
    </script>
</body>
</html>
```

## Understanding the CSS

Our custom CSS handles the chat-specific styling:

```css
.chat-box {
    height: 400px;           /* Fixed height */
    overflow-y: auto;        /* Scroll when messages overflow */
    border: 1px solid #dee2e6;
    border-radius: 10px;     /* Rounded corners */
    padding: 20px;
    background-color: white;
}
```

### Message Styling

```css
.user-message {
    background-color: #007bff;  /* Blue background */
    color: white;
    margin-left: auto;          /* Pushes to the right side */
}

.bot-message {
    background-color: #e9ecef;  /* Grey background */
    color: #333;
}
```

The `margin-left: auto` is a CSS trick to align user messages to the right, while bot messages stay on the left.

## Understanding the JavaScript

The JavaScript handles sending messages and receiving responses:

### Getting DOM Elements

```javascript
const chatForm = document.getElementById('chat-form');
const messageInput = document.getElementById('message-input');
const chatBox = document.getElementById('chat-box');
```

We store references to the HTML elements we need to interact with.

### Adding Messages

```javascript
function addMessage(text, isUser) {
    const messageDiv = document.createElement('div');
    messageDiv.className = `message ${isUser ? 'user-message' : 'bot-message'}`;
    messageDiv.textContent = text;
    chatBox.appendChild(messageDiv);
    chatBox.scrollTop = chatBox.scrollHeight;  // Auto-scroll to bottom
}
```

This function:
1. Creates a new `<div>` element
2. Sets the appropriate CSS class (user or bot style)
3. Sets the text content
4. Adds it to the chat box
5. Scrolls to show the new message

## The Fetch API

The most important part is sending messages to our Flask backend:

```javascript
const response = await fetch('/chat', {
    method: 'POST',
    headers: {
        'Content-Type': 'application/json',
    },
    body: JSON.stringify({ message: message })
});

const data = await response.json();
```

### Breaking It Down

| Part | Purpose |
|------|----------|
| `fetch('/chat', ...)` | Send a request to the `/chat` URL |
| `method: 'POST'` | Use POST method (sending data) |
| `headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' }` | Tell Flask we're sending JSON |
| `body: JSON.stringify({ message: message })` | Convert our data to JSON format |
| `await response.json()` | Convert the response from JSON |

### The async/await Pattern

```javascript
chatForm.addEventListener('submit', async function(e) {
    e.preventDefault();  // Stop page from reloading
    // ...
});
```

- `async` marks the function as asynchronous (it will wait for things)
- `await` pauses execution until the fetch completes
- `e.preventDefault()` stops the form from reloading the page

## Adding Error Handling

Notice how we handle errors:

```javascript
try {
    const response = await fetch('/chat', ...);
    const data = await response.json();
    addMessage(data.response, false);
} catch (error) {
    addMessage('Sorry, something went wrong. Please try again.', false);
    console.error('Error:', error);
}
```

### Why Error Handling Matters

| Scenario | Without Error Handling | With Error Handling |
|----------|----------------------|--------------------|
| Server is down | Page freezes, no feedback | User sees error message |
| Network issues | Silent failure | User knows to try again |
| Invalid response | JavaScript crashes | Graceful fallback |

> 🔒 **Best Practice**: Always wrap API calls in try/catch to handle failures gracefully.
